  "description": [
    "FIVE ITALYS FASCISM IS BELIEVED DUE FOR SHAKING UP Special to The Ieader ROME The first anniversary of Fascism in Italy provided a text for many editorials in which the Idea of crisis in Fascism recurred regard less of the party affiliations of the papers There is no doubt about the crisis in Italian Fascism On the surface it may look like a feud between the metropolitan and provincial Fascist leaders in reality It is the begin ning of a struggle between revolu tionary and reactionary Fascists Former Socialist Mussolini be came the leader of reactionary im perialism but the labor union men Socialists and communists who were forced willynilly into Fascist clubs did not change their minds as easily us Mussolini did Wanted Real Action Most of the young men who joined the Fascist clubs were romantic ideal ists who knew little or nothing of social development The Socialists Communists and Syndicalists who joined were temperamentally unlit for constructive reform work such us must be done in preparation for So cialism For a while the differences between reactionaries and revolutionists slum bered in the Fascist organization but they did not die out The first anniversary of Facism finds them"
  ],
